    {
      "id": "a2bd6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Department of African American Studies at UCLA continues in the legacy of developing global citizen-scholars focused on analyzing and writing about the lived experiences and freedom dreams of people throughout Africa and the African Diaspora. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following by the end of spring before transfer: One course in African American Studies or One Civilizations of Africa course. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https://afam.ucla.edu and https://admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Department of African American Studies at UCLA continues in the legacy of developing global citizen-scholars focused on analyzing and writing about the lived experiences and freedom dreams of people throughout Africa and the African Diaspora.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One course in African American Studies or</li><li>One Civilizations of Africa course.</li></ul><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://afam.ucla.edu</u> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://admission.ucla.edu</u>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    }
